      "instruction": "<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Peel the <strong>garlic</strong></span></p>\n<p>Add the <strong>drained chickpeas</strong> to a<strong> food processor</strong> with the<strong> tahini </strong>and <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>peeled garlic</strong> (Don't like raw garlic? Go easy!)</span></p>\n<p>Add the <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>juice</strong></span> of 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span><strong> lemon</strong>, 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and 50ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [100ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong></p>\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Add a</span> very generous pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and whizz for 1 min or until smooth – this is your <strong>hummus</strong></p>\n<p> </p>",
